## 1) Scope (MUST)

- Implement a framework-agnostic TS library (no React dependency).
- Provide both **popup** and **iframe modal** open modes.
- Unify results via **postMessage**:
  - Messages: `EDGE_READY`, `EDGE_COMPLETE {token,status}`, `EDGE_CANCEL`, `EDGE_ERROR {error}`.
- **Origin filtering**: only accept messages from `allowedOrigin` (default = `new URL(edgeUrl).origin`).
- Token persistence in `localStorage` with safe try/catch.
- **Insecure no-session mode** (for hackathon): when enabled, **do not** call any session/token endpoint—just open `/kyc`.

---

## 2) Non-Goals (MUST NOT)

- No secret keys (`sk_...`) in the browser.
- No server code, databases, or webhooks here.
- No bundlers (Rollup/Webpack/Vite) for the lib build—**use `tsc` only**.
- No external UI frameworks; use DOM APIs for modal/iframe.
- No analytics/telemetry.

---

## 3) Public API (stable)

```typescript
export type KycStatus = 'unknown' | 'pending' | 'verified' | 'rejected';

export type InitOptions = {
  edgeUrl: string;          // e.g., https://edge.example.com
  clientId: string;         // integrator/app id
  storageKey?: string;      // default 'kyc_token'
  allowedOrigin?: string;   // default origin(edgeUrl)
  onStatusChange?: (s: KycStatus) => void;
  // Future-friendly (scaffold only):
  publishableKey?: string;
  createSessionUrl?: string;
  getClientToken?: () => Promise<{ session_id: string; client_secret: string }>;
  // Hackathon mode: DO NOT pre-call anything; just open /kyc
  insecureNoSession?: boolean; // default false
};

export type StartKycOptions = {
  locale?: string;
  theme?: 'light'|'dark'|'auto';
  loginHint?: string;
  openMode?: 'iframe'|'popup'; // default 'iframe'
  insecure?: boolean;          // force no-session for this call
};

export type KycResult =
 | { ok: true; status: KycStatus; token?: string }
 | { ok: false; error: string };

export type EdgeMessage =
 | { type: 'EDGE_READY' }
 | { type: 'EDGE_COMPLETE'; token: string; status: KycStatus }
 | { type: 'EDGE_CANCEL' }
 | { type: 'EDGE_ERROR'; error: string };
```

**Public functions:**
- `init(options: InitOptions): void`
- `startKyc(opts?: StartKycOptions): Promise<KycResult>`
- `requireKyc(mode?: 'modal'|'reject', openMode?: 'popup'|'iframe'): Promise<boolean>`
- `checkStatus(signal?: AbortSignal): Promise<KycStatus>`
- `loginIfVerified(): Promise<boolean>`
- `getToken(): string | null`
- `logout(): void`

**Backward-compat:** only additive changes to this API.

---

## 4) File Layout (MUST)

```
packages/kyc-client/
  package.json        // "type":"module", "main":"dist/index.js", "types":"dist/index.d.ts"
  tsconfig.json       // strict TS, ES2021 target, ES2020 module, DOM lib, declarations, outDir: dist
  src/
    index.ts          // exports default singleton + types
    client.ts         // KycClient class (core logic)
    core/types.ts     // public types only
    core/storage.ts   // safe localStorage helpers
    transport/edgeApi.ts // /status (and future session helpers, behind flags)
    ui/overlay.ts     // modal + iframe creation/destruction
    ui/popup.ts       // centered popup opener
```

